{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Debt scolds hate good fiscal news so much that most Americans haven&#8217;t heard that the deficit plunge of the past several years continues.", "abstract": "Paul Krugman Op-Ed column examines why there has been so little fanfare surrounding fact that deficit has fallen significantly and continues to fall; blames news media coverage of deficit, which plays up bad news and downplays good news, if it is reported at all; criticizes deficit scolds, who in fact love big budget deficits because fears of fiscal crisis are their best hope of getting big cuts in social programs, which is their ultimate goal.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "27", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Paul", "role": "reported", "lastname": "KRUGMAN", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By PAUL KRUGMAN", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/10/10/opinion/paul-krugman-secret-deficit-lovers.html", "lead_paragraph": "Debt scolds hate good fiscal news so much that most Americans haven&#8217;t heard that the deficit plunge of the past several years continues.", "headline": {"main": "Secret Deficit Lovers", "print_headline": "Secret Deficit Lovers", "content_kicker": "Op-Ed Columnist", "kicker": "Op-Ed Columnist"}, "_id": "54381b0438f0d83c143b8a2e", "word_count": "799", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/10/30/opinion/krugman-new-1114/krugman-new-1114-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/10/30/opinion/krugman-new-1114/krugman-new-1114-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 900, "url": "images/2014/10/30/opinion/krugman-new-1114/krugman-new-1114-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/10/30/opinion/krugman-new-1114/krugman-new-1114-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "900"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "ima